headline: Why Expeditors (EXPD) Stock Is Trading Lower Today
summary: Shares of logistics and freight forwarding company Expeditors (NYSE:EXPD) fell 2.8% in the afternoon session after investors reacted to an 'underweight' rating from Barclays and digested ongoing concerns about the company's weak financial performance.

headline: Expeditors (EXPD): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q2 Earnings?
summary: Although Expeditors (currently trading at $124.05 per share) has gained 6.6% over the last six months, it has trailed the S&P 500’s 16.8% return during that period. This may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
